videoSnippet.title: Cancer Ruined his Tournament, But The Prize for Beauty, as Always, He Took With Him
videoSnippet.description:
#agadmator Check out more Amazing Nezhy games here https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2tnwzOV_PEY&list=PLDnx7w_xuguEp6SoxMSneptFu4G3noM7q

Also, check out Tal vs Suetin - Not Bad For A Dead Man https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2gPs3yG7T1E

Vladimir I Karasev vs Rashid Gibiatovich Nezhmetdinov
Latvian open (1973), Daugavpils 
English Opening: Symmetrical. Anti-Benoni Variation Spielmann Defense (A32)

1. Nf3 Nf6 2. c4 c5 3. d4 cd4 4. Nd4 e6 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. Nb5 O-O 7. Bf4 d5 8. a3 Bc3 9. Nc3 d4 10. Nb5 a6 11. Nc7 Ra7 12. Nb5 ab5 13. Bb8 bc4 14. Ba7 Qa5 15. Qd2 Qa7 16. e3 d3 17. g3 Ne4 18. Qb4 d2 19. Ke2 Qa6 20. Kf3 Qc6 21. Ke2 Qd5 22. Rd1 e5 23. h3 b6 24. Rg1 c3 25. bc3 Nc3

I am both sad and pleased that in his last tournament, Rashid
 Gibiatovich came to my home in Latvia. He did not take first place, but
 the prize for beauty, as always, he took with him. Players die, tournaments are 
forgotten, but the works of great artists are left behind them to live on forever.

Mikhail Tal
